      <title>All I Did Was Change His Food!</title>
      <description>My dog Rusty is very lazy. He was sleeping all of the time. He is turning 2 this month. I walk him routinely, I take him outside to play ball. I couldn't figure out why he was so lethargic.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;He is very picky with his dog food, I found only one dog food that he likes. One day I was in the super market and I decided to change his dog food. I had gotten him a all natural dry dog food. I mix it in with his wet food and he loves it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;He is now full of energy and always on the go. I can't believe that by just getting a better dog food would increase his energy. I found this book on the &lt;span class="blsp-spelling-corrected" id="SPELLING_ERROR_0"&gt;Internet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://michelleo1.68dogs.hop.clickbank.net/"&gt; 68 Dog Food Ingredients To Die For&lt;/a&gt; and it lists 68 harmful ingredients found in commercial dog foods. I couldn't believe how many manufactures of dog food have one or more of these ingredients in them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you would like to know more I recommend this &lt;a href="http://michelleo1.68dogs.hop.clickbank.net/"&gt;book&lt;/a&gt;. My Rusty dog has more energy and I feel like I just did something good for him.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Have a happy and healthier dog just by changing his food.&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="http://del.icio.us/feeds/js/michj?title=my%20del.icio.us;icon;name;showadd"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
